article.headline: Richmond 71, Duquesne 67
article.story: RICHMOND, Va. -- David Gonzalvez scored 16 points to lead the Spiders to a 71-67 victory over Duquesne on Wednesday night. Trailing by 15 points, the Spiders (12-12, 4-5 Atlantic 10 Conference) went on a 20-5 run sparked by three 3-pointers from Gonzalvez to tie the game at 40-40. Richmond took its first lead, 57-54 with 7:54 left on a Ryan Butler 3-pointer and the Dukes (15-8, 6-4) never regained the advantage. Duquesne started the game with a 12-0 lead thanks to three Richmond turnovers. The Dukes then built the lead to as many as 35-20 on a Saunders layup with 3:51 left in the first half. Kevin Anderson scored 14 points and Ryan Butler added 13 for the Spiders. Ryan Butler and Jarhon Giddings chipped in 11 each. Damian Saunders and Aaron Jackson scored 14 points apiece for the Dukes. It was Richmond's 12th straight win in the series.
